commits.message: fixed Makefile.am to include appstream data to dist
Moved appstream data to PREFIX/share/metainfo/
Added Appdata files, fixed some typos, completed gitignore
Fixed --version
make build reproducible, increase version number
New version 0.1.3 now support --verbose
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:bwildenhain/air-quality-sensor
Added --verb (gives serial no of uplink hub)
Also print bus no when using a recent libusb version
Include src/manpage.include in dist-target

Now using help2man to generate manpage

Also listed bugtracker on github in --version.
Added test for help2man
Added links to packaged+signed source archive.

air10.c no longer prints "BLINK", when no data are received, but
"NO_DATA", as sensor also gives a value of 450, when it cannot detect
any pollution, fixed documentation (double "the"), added github URL,
changed version number in configure.ac
Now refering the vendors name (not resellers brand name), version set to 0.1.1, fixed autogen.sh
Implemented parameter handling using getopt (currently only --help and --version are supported), added manpage
Reformatted according to GNU coding standards.

-Use GNU Autotools
-Made air10.c compatible with older versions of libusb-1.0
-Properly formatted URL in README.md
This is version 0.1
Added usage output to air01/10.c, cleaned up makefile, activated compiler optimization
Added license information to source code, wrote README.

Merge github.com:bwildenhain/air-quality-probe

Conflicts:
	.gitignore
Initial commit
